---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Cigna Global in Colombia', level: 2 },
  { id: 'why-cigna', text: 'Why Cigna for Colombia', level: 2 },
  { id: 'plans-and-pricing', text: 'Plans and Pricing', level: 2 },
  { id: 'coverage-details', text: 'Coverage Details', level: 2 },
  { id: 'nomad-considerations', text: 'Digital Nomad Considerations', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Health Insurance in Colombia', href: '/countries/colombia/insurance' },
  { title: 'Cigna Global Review', href: '/providers/cigna-global' },
  { title: 'Cigna vs Allianz', href: '/compare/cigna-global-vs-allianz-care' },
];

const planColumns = [
  { key: 'plan', header: 'Plan' },
  { key: 'coverage', header: 'Coverage' },
  { key: 'price', header: 'Price (Age 35)' },
];

const planRows = [
  { plan: 'Silver', coverage: 'Core inpatient', price: '$140-180/mo' },
  { plan: 'Gold', coverage: 'Inpatient + outpatient', price: '$180-230/mo' },
  { plan: 'Platinum', coverage: 'Comprehensive', price: '$230-280/mo' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Cigna Global Health Insurance in Colombia"
  description="Guide to Cigna Global international health insurance for expats and digital nomads in Colombia. Coverage for Medellín and Bogotá hospitals."
  headline="Cigna Global in Colombia"
  subheadline="Premium international coverage for Colombia's growing expat community. Strong hospital network and worldwide flexibility."
  heroBackgroundImage="/images/countries/colombia-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Get a Cigna Quote"
  ctaButtonHref="/providers/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Cigna Global in Colombia</h2>
  <p>
    Cigna Global is a strong choice for expats seeking comprehensive coverage in Colombia. With established relationships at Colombia's top hospitals and worldwide coverage, Cigna addresses the needs of both long-term expats and mobile digital nomads.
  </p>
  <p>
    For those who travel frequently or want the option to seek care elsewhere, Cigna's global network provides flexibility that local insurers can't match.
  </p>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-4 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-600">$180-280</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">Monthly (Age 35)</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-600">Direct Billing</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">Major Colombian hospitals</p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-4 text-center">
      <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-600">Worldwide</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">Coverage included</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <CTABox
    title="Get Your Cigna Colombia Quote"
    description="Comprehensive coverage for Colombia expats and digital nomads."
    buttonText="Get Quote"
    buttonHref="/providers/cigna-global"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <h2 id="why-cigna">Why Cigna for Colombia</h2>
  <p>
    Cigna Global stands out for Colombia expats for several reasons:
  </p>

  <h3>Hospital Network</h3>
  <p>
    Cigna has relationships with Colombia's leading hospitals:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Fundación Santa Fe (Bogotá):</strong> JCI-accredited, direct billing available</li>
    <li><strong>Hospital Pablo Tobón Uribe (Medellín):</strong> Top-rated facility in network</li>
    <li><strong>Clínica Las Américas (Medellín):</strong> Popular with expats, direct billing</li>
    <li><strong>Fundación Cardioinfantil (Bogotá):</strong> Specialized cardiac care</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Digital Nomad Friendly</h3>
  <p>
    Cigna works well for Colombia's nomad community because:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Meets digital nomad visa insurance requirements</li>
    <li>Worldwide coverage for frequent travelers</li>
    <li>Easy online claims and member portal</li>
    <li>24/7 support for emergencies anywhere</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Flexibility</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Add or remove US coverage as needed</li>
    <li>Adjust deductibles to control costs</li>
    <li>Upgrade plans without new underwriting</li>
    <li>Maintain coverage if you move countries</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="plans-and-pricing">Plans and Pricing</h2>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={planColumns} rows={planRows} />
  </div>

  <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 italic">
    Prices shown for healthy 35-year-old. Actual premiums depend on age, health history, selected coverage, and deductible.
  </p>

  <h3>Cost Factors</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Age:</strong> Premiums increase with age, significantly after 50</li>
    <li><strong>US coverage:</strong> Adding US coverage increases premiums 30-50%</li>
    <li><strong>Deductible:</strong> Higher deductibles ($2,500-$5,000) can reduce premiums 20-30%</li>
    <li><strong>Area of coverage:</strong> Americas-only is cheaper than worldwide</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-3">Colombia Cost Advantage</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800">
      Because healthcare costs are lower in Colombia than in the US or Europe, Cigna's premiums for Colombia-based expats tend to be quite competitive. You're getting premium coverage at reasonable rates.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="coverage-details">Coverage Details</h2>

  <h3>What's Covered</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Inpatient:</strong> Hospital stays, surgery, ICU</li>
    <li><strong>Outpatient:</strong> Doctor visits, specialists, diagnostics (Gold+)</li>
    <li><strong>Emergency:</strong> Worldwide emergency coverage</li>
    <li><strong>Evacuation:</strong> Medical evacuation to nearest appropriate facility</li>
    <li><strong>Cancer treatment:</strong> Full coverage at network facilities</li>
    <li><strong>Chronic conditions:</strong> Covered after waiting period</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Limitations</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Pre-existing conditions: 2-year moratorium or underwriting</li>
    <li>Mental health: Limited coverage, varies by plan</li>
    <li>Dental/vision: Optional add-on, limited benefits</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="nomad-considerations">Digital Nomad Considerations</h2>

  <h3>Visa Compliance</h3>
  <p>
    Cigna Global meets Colombia's digital nomad visa insurance requirements. You can provide your policy documents as proof of coverage during the visa application.
  </p>

  <h3>Frequent Travel</h3>
  <p>
    If you're based in Colombia but travel often to other countries, Cigna's worldwide coverage means you're protected wherever you go—no need for separate travel insurance.
  </p>

  <h3>Portability</h3>
  <p>
    If you decide to move from Colombia to another country, Cigna moves with you. No need to cancel and reapply—just update your country of residence.
  </p>

  <CTABox
    title="Compare Cigna Plans for Colombia"
    description="Find the right coverage level for your needs."
    buttonText="Get Quote"
    buttonHref="/providers/cigna-global"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> Prices and coverage details are estimates based on typical scenarios. Get a personalized quote for accurate pricing based on your age, health, and coverage needs.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
